node.text:
Simple, easy and fun experiment for learning to wash hands effectively 🧼 The items we used were: 🧼 dish washing soap mixed with black/blue food coloring or acrylic paint. 🧼 Then, use gloves 🧤 so the paint/ food coloring does not stain hands and indicates which areas we missed ✨
🧼 the bin is filled with water only! 
Supervision is advised. This experiment is easy peasy and a great learning experience, kids activity and experiment for learning to wash our hands properly in a fun way (water play and sensory play) 🤗
.
.

node.text:
It’s here! A simple early learning Valentine’s Day Busy Book! 💖
.
.
What’s covered? 💖emotions 💖colors 💖uppercase/lowercase letters
💖writing 💖counting
💖 ten frames
💖shapes
💖matching activities 💖pattern match 💖counting and writing numbers .
.
And any other fun activities you can come up with with the pieces. For example adding them to a sensory bin or a fun find the pair activity 💕
.
.
This is by far my favorite busy book and I hope you enjoy it as much as we have! 💕💖
.
.
To those who are part of the subscription, you received this yesterday! You can also purchase this individually by going to https://www.activelittles.com/products/ .
.
To learn more about our subscription, just follow the link mentioned above as well! 💖
.
.
Happy Learning! .
.

Giant Bubbles Using A Hoola Hoop .
.
Its spring time and bubbles are a perfect outdoor kids activity. Take it up a notch by making these ginormous bubbles with one special ingredient.. .
.
What you'll need to create these gigantic bubbles:
🌼 wading pool
🌼 distilled water (4 gallons)
🌼 dish soap (6 to 8 cups) we used an entire bottle of dawn dish soap

🌼insert water, syrup and dishsoap into wading pool
🌼 mix it up 🌼 bring out hoola hoops and start making bubbles!!
.
.
